 = [[Iowa Hawkeyes football|Iowa]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 2\n | pick       = 43\n | player     = [[Jahlani Tavai]]\n | position   = [[Linebacker|LB]]\n | college    = [[Hawaii Rainbow Warriors football|Hawaii]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 3\n | pick       = 81\n | player     = [[Will Harris (American football)|Will Harris]]\n | position   = [[Safety (gridiron football position)|S]]\n | college    = [[Boston College Eagles football|Boston College]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 4\n | pick       = 117\n | player     = [[Austin Bryant]]\n | position   = [[Defensive end|DE]]\n | college    = [[Clemson Tigers football|Clemson]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 5\n | pick       = 146\n | player     = [[Amani Oruwariye]]\n | position   = [[Cornerback|CB]]\n | college    = [[Penn State Nittany Lions football|Penn State]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 6\n | pick       = 184\n | player     = [[Travis Fulgham]]\n | position   = [[Wide receiver|WR]]\n | college    = [[Old Dominion Monarchs football|Old Dominion]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 6\n | pick       = 186\n | player     = [[Ty Johnson (American football)|Ty Johnson]]\n | position   = [[Running back|RB]]\n | college    = [[Maryland Terrapins football|Maryland]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 7\n | pick       = 224\n | player     = [[Isaac Nauta]]\n | position   = [[Tight End|TE]]\n | college    = [[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = \n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 7\n | pick       = 229\n | player     = [[P. J. Johnson]]\n | position   = [[Defensive Tackle|DT]]\n | college    = [[Arizona Wildcats football|Arizona]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = \n | probowl    = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft end\n | hof = no\n}}\n\n====Draft trades====\n*The Lions acquired a fourth-round selection (No. 114) from the [[New England Patriots]] in the [[2018 NFL Draft|2018 draft]] in exchange for a third-round selection in the [[2019 NFL Draft|2019 draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2018/04/28/detroit-lions-nfl-draft/561292002/|title=Detroit Lions trade up, pick Alabama DE Da'Shawn Hand in NFL draft Round 4|newspaper=[[Detroit Free Press]]|first=Carlos|last=Monarrez|date=April 28, 2018|accessdate=April 28, 2018}}</ref>\n*The Lions received a third round selection from the [[Philadelphia Eagles]] in exchange for wide receiver [[Golden Tate]].<ref>[http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/25127780/lions-trade-wide-receiver-golden-tate-eagles Wide receiver Golden Tate heading from Lions to Eagles] ESPN, October 30, 2018</ref>\n*The Lions acquired a third-round selection (No. 81) from the [[Minnesota Vikings]] in exchange for their original third-round selection (No. 88) and a sixth-round selection (No. 204).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2019/04/26/detroit-lions-will-harris-2019-nfl-draft/3593387002/ |title=Detroit Lions take DB Will Harris in Round 3 of 2019 NFL draft |newspaper=Detroit Free Press |first=Carlos |last=Monarrez |date=April 26, 2019 |access-date=April 26, 2019}}</ref>\n*The Lions acquired a fourth-round selection (No. 117) and a sixth-round selection (No. 186) from the [[Atlanta Falcons]] in exchange for their original fourth-round selection (No. 111).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2019/04/27/detroit-lions-trade-down-fourth-round-gain-sixth-rounder/3599120002/ |title=Lions trade down in fourth round, draft Clemson DE Austin Bryant |newspaper=The Detroit News |first=Justin |last=Rogers |date=April 27, 2019 |accessdate=April 27, 2019}}</ref>\n*The [[Miami Dolphins]] traded a conditional seventh-round selection to Detroit in exchange for defensive tackle [[Akeem Spence]].<ref>[http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/23396165/miami-dolphins-obtain-defensive-tackle-akeem-spence-trade-detroit-lions Lions trade DT Akeem Spence to Dolphins] ESPN, May 3, 2018</ref>\n*Detroit traded a fifth-round selection to the [[New York Giants]] in exchange for defensive tackle [[Damon Harrison]]. The condition was that the Giants would receive the higher of Detroit or San Francisco's 5th round selections.<ref>{{cite web|title=Giants trade DT Damon Harrison to Lions for 5th-round pick|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/25068826/giants-trade-dt-damon-harrison-lions-5th-round-pick|date=October 25, 2018|accessdate=November 13, 2018}}</ref>\n*The [[San Francisco 49ers]] traded their fifth-round selection to Detroit in exchange for guard [[Laken Tomlinson]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Michael|title=Lions trade former first-round pick Laken Tomlinson to 49ers for fifth-round pick|url=http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2017/08/31/lions-trade-former-first-round-pick-laken-tomlinson-to-49ers-for-fifth-round-pick/|work=NFL.com|date=August 31, 2017|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Staff==\n{{NFL final staff\n|Year=2019\n|TeamName=Detroit Lions\n|Front Office=\n*Owner/chairwoman \u2013 [[Martha Firestone Ford]]\n*Vice chairwoman \u2013 [[Martha Ford Morse]]\n*Vice chairman \u2013 [[William Clay Ford Jr.]]\n*Vice chairwoman \u2013 [[Sheila Ford Hamp]]\n*Vice chairwoman \u2013 [[Elizabeth Ford Kontulis]]\n*Team President \u2013 [[Rod Wood]]\n*Executive vice president & general manager \u2013 [[Bob Quinn (American football)|Bob Quinn]]\n*Senior vice president of administration, CFO \u2013 [[Allison Maki]]\n*Vice president of football administration \u2013 [[Mike Disner]]\n*Vice president of player personne