ord]] \u2013 30/45, 364 yards, 4 TD, INT\n'''Top rushers'''\n*MIN \u2013 [[Dalvin Cook]] \u2013 25 rushes, 142 yards, 2 TD\n*DET \u2013 [[J. D. McKissic]] \u2013 5 rushes, 29 yards\n'''Top receivers'''\n*MIN \u2013 [[Stefon Diggs]] \u2013 7 receptions, 142 yards\n*DET \u2013 [[Danny Amendola]] \u2013 8 receptions, 105 yards\n}}\nIn week 7, the Lions hosted another divisional [[Lions\u2013Vikings rivalry|rival]], the [[2019 Minnesota Vikings season|Minnesota Vikings]]. The Lions scored 14 points in the first quarter via two touchdown passes from [[Matthew Stafford]] to [[Marvin Jones (wide receiver)|Marvin Jones]] from 16-yards, and three-yards, respectively. The Vikings responded with a 25-yard touchdown pass from [[Kirk Cousins]] to [[Adam Thielen]]. The Vikings scored 14 points in the second quarter via a one-yard touchdown pass from Cousins to [[Bisi Johnson]] and an eight-yard touchdown run from [[Dalvin Cook]] to take their first lead of the game. The Lions responded with a 10-yard touchdown pass from Stafford to Jones, tying the score at 21\u201321 at halftime. Minnesota regained the lead in the third quarter via a five-yard touchdown pass from Cousins to [[C. J. Ham]]. The Lions responded with a 46-yard field goal by [[Matt Prater]]. The Vikings scored 14 points in the fourth quarter via a 15-yard touchdown pass from Cousins to [[Kyle Rudolph]] and a four-yard touchdown run from Cook. The Lions responded with a two-yard touchdown pass from Stafford to Jones, making the final score 42\u201330 in favor of Minnesota, for Detroit's third consecutive loss. Jones became the first Lions player with four touchdown receptions in a game since [[Cloyce Box]] did so against the [[1950 Baltimore Colts season|Baltimore Colts]] in [[1950 Detroit Lions season|1950]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2019/10/20/detroit-lions-marvin-jones-four-touchdowns-vikings/4048635002/ |title=Detroit Lions' Marvin Jones makes history, dazzles with 4 TD catches in loss |newspaper=Detroit Free Press |first=Carlos |last=Monarrez |date=October 20, 2019 |access-date=October 20, 2019}}</ref> Stafford became the fastest quarterback to throw for 40,000 yards, reaching the milestone in 147 games.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2019/10/20/detroit-lions-matthew-stafford-fastest-40-k-career-passing-yards/4045636002/ |title=Lions' Matthew Stafford becomes fastest to 40,000 career passing yards |first=Justin |last=Rogers |newspaper=The Detroit News |date=October 20, 2019 |access-date=October 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Week 8: vs. New York Giants====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n|titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Detroit Lions|year=2019|border=2}};text-align:center;\n|state=autocollapse\n|title=Week Eight: New York Giants at Detroit Lions&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n|date=October 27\n|time=1:00&nbsp;p.m. EDT\n|road=Giants\n|R1=0|R2=13|R3=6|R4=7\n|home='''Lions'''\n|H1=14|H2=3|H3=7|H4=7\n|stadium=Ford Field, Detroit, Michigan\n|attendance=58,509\n|weather=None (indoor stadium)\n|referee=Scott Novak\n|TV=Fox\n|TVAnnouncers=[[Kenny Albert]], Charles Davis and Pam Oliver\n|reference=[https://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2019102703/2019/REG8/giants@lions Recap], [https://nflcdns.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/58010/DET_Gamebook.pdf Game Book]\n|scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*DET \u2013 [[Devon Kennard]] 13-yard fumble return ([[Matt Prater]] kick), 7:12. ''Lions 7\u20130.''\n*DET \u2013 [[Marvin Hall]] 49-yard pass from [[Matthew Stafford]] (Matt Prater kick), 2:31. ''Lions 14\u20130. '''Drive: 6 plays, 71 yards, 3:01.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*NYG \u2013 [[Darius Slayton]] 22-yard pass from [[Daniel Jones (American football)|Daniel Jones]] ([[Aldrick Rosas]] kick), 12:27. ''Lions 14\u20137. '''Drive: 10 plays, 88 yards, 5:04.'''''\n*NYG \u2013 Darius Slayton 28-yard pass from Daniel Jones, 4:39. ''Lions 14\u201313. '''Drive: 8 plays, 57 yards, 3:30.'''''\n*DET \u2013 Matt Prater 52-yard field goal, 0:20. ''Lions 17\