 Country Belle ||     ||  scr        ||    W J Morland    || A Hendricksen|| 4:35.6\n|-\n|1914 || Win Soon||      ||  6 secs          ||    Mr. Stevenson, Mr. McMath || A Pringle|| 4:31\n|-\n|1913 || Ravenschild ||     ||  6 secs       ||    J McCutcheon   || N L Price ||4:35.4\n|-\n|1912 || Albert H ||     ||  8 secs          ||    M Maher        || A Hendricksen ||4:48.8\n|-\n|1911 || Lady Clare ||     ||  4 secs        ||    W F Clinton    || J Brankin ||4:38\n|-\n|1910 || Wildwood Junior ||     ||  scr      ||    W Kerr         || W Kerr|| 4:33\n|-\n|1909 || Wildwood Junior||      ||  5 secs   ||    W Kerr         || W Kerr ||4:39\n|-\n|1908 || Durbar ||     ||  scr               ||    H F Nicoll     || A Pringle ||4:36\n|-\n|1907 || Marian ||     ||  9 secs            ||    S E Tasker     || J Tasker|| 5:16.4\n|-\n|1906 || Belmont M ||     ||  4 secs         ||    J Mills        || A G Milsom ||4:46\n|-\n|1905 || Birchmark ||     ||  7 secs         ||    Allendale Stock Farm Co. ||  D J Price ||5:17.6\n|-\n|1904 || Monte Carlo (T)||      ||  7 secs   ||    T Yarr ||  B Edwards ||4:44.4\n|}\n{{refbegin}}* won the [[New Zealand Free For All]] same year{{refend}}\n\n== Other associated races ==\n\nThe horses that contest the New Zealand Cup commonly compete in various races that have become seen as traditional lead in races.  The winner of the New Zealand Cup is usually one that wins or performs strongly in these races.       \n\nOn the Friday following the New Zealand Cup, Canterbury Anniversary day, many of the same horses will contest the [[New Zealand Free For All]]. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! width=\"30px\" | Year<br>\n! width=\"80px\" | Hannon Memorial (2600m) Oamaru<br>\n! width=\"80px\" | Ashburton Flying Stakes (2400m) Ashburton<br>\n! width=\"80px\" | Kaikoura Cup (2400m) Kaikoura<br>\n! width=\"80px\" | New Zealand Cup (3200m) Addington<br>\n! width=\"80px\" | [[New Zealand Free For All]] (1609m) Addington<br>\n! width=\"80px\" | Notes<b